    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Would be nice to be able to define functions that take arbitrary dimensional `memoryview`s. Perhaps could use syntax like `double[...] a`. Interestingly this comes up in CEP 517 in [this section]( https://github.com/cython/cython/wiki/enhancements-array#the-dimension-specifiers ) and a few SO questions.\r\n\r\nref: https://stackoverflow.com/q/29484943\r\nref: https://stackoverflow.com/q/33316131",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Sounds like a nice feature. A few comments:\r\n\r\n- Would probably also suggest to support a minimum dimensionality as in `double[:, :, ...]` for \"at least two dimensions\" (I guess).\r\n- There is currently a hard default limit of 8 dimensions, which can be configured at compile time.\r\n- The main difficulty is probably to fix all the places where the compiler assumes a known dimensionality.",
