        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I was hoping to try accelerating some code where I use tensor networks, so having arbitrary dimensional memoryview support would be amazing.\r\n\r\nI looked through `Cython/Compiler` and I see two main uses of `ndim`:\r\n\r\n1. broadcasting (there seems to be one instance of this)\r\n2. validation (there are various checks that the dimensions are not larger than the configured maximum dimension)\r\n\r\nIts possible I missed some cases, but based on what I saw it appears there aren't a lot of places that rely on ndim being defined.\r\n",
            "created_at": "2021-02-11T18:39:02Z",
